From: experintellia <280144245+experintellia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 23:55:06 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 51/64] web-app: gate the composer completion menu behind an
 experimental setting

The :emoji: completion menu (patch 0049) now only activates when the new
`experimentalCompletionMenu` desktop setting is on. Off by default, opt in
under Settings -> Advanced -> Experimental features.

Mirrors the existing off-by-default `linkPreviewSuggestions` flag: one key in
DesktopSettingsType + getDefaultState(), one DesktopSettingsSwitch, and the
flag plumbed from Composer to both ComposerMessageInput instances. The single
gate is an early return in refreshCompletion() -- the only path that opens the
menu -- so detection, key ownership, and rendering are all inert when off.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
